item.title: Containers
item.description: Containers # Lists # A list is a container that can hold a sequence of information (usually related information). Lists can hold any Python values (not the same behaviour in every language), including other lists/objects etc. empty = [] # empty list B = ["Ben", "Box", "", "Bufy"] # Strings numbers = [2, 5, 7] # Integers floats = [2.0, 3.5, 7.5] # Floats nested = [[2, 3], 3, 4] # Storing a list inside a list mixed = ["Hi", 2, 3.
